
ACM = AWS Certificate Manager
[youtube - https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=pTQrAZbHmRU ]

- ACM is a service that lets you easily provision, manage, and deploy public/private Secure Sockets Layer(SSL) & Transport Layer Security (TLS) certificates. 
- Use for AWS services and your internal connected resources. 
- ACM SSL/TLS certificates are used to secure network communications. 
- ACM Establish the identity of websites over the Internet as well as resources on private networks.
- ACM removes the time-consuming manual process of purchasing, uploading, and renewing SSL/TLS certificates.

The ACM SSL/TLS certificates can deploy on ACM-integrated AWS resources like -	
	- Elastic Load Balancers
	- Amazon CloudFront distributions APIs on API Gateway,


- SSL/TLS certificate provisioned by ACM are free. these certificates are easy to provision with a few button clicks
- Public and private certificates provisioned through ACM for use with ACM-integrated services are free.
- You have to pay only for the AWS resources you create to run your application. 

- ACM certificate can also be renewals, but cannon be dowloaded.
- they can only be used with AWS resources such as elastic load balancer, amazone cloudfront, Amazon CloudFront distributions APIs on API Gateway.  




Steps to launch ACM SSL/TLS Certificate -
	1. add your repective domain name
	2. select validation method
		 (DNS validation/Email validation)
	3. complete the"I approve " email validation from domain mailstation, if you selected an email validation
	4. review & validate the request.
	5. launch the certificate.
	
	
	
	
